<DOC><DOCNO> AP890801-0246 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-01-89 1248EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Bridgestone-Firestone     08-01 0124</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bridgestone-Firestone,0132</SECOND><HEAD>Bridgestone Consolidates Tire Headquarters In Akron</HEAD><DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bridgestone Corp., which last year mergedwith Firestone Tire andamp; Rubber Co., said today it was consolidatingits tire business under a new name and corporate headquarters.   The merged company will be known as Bridgestone-Firestone Inc.,the company said.   Although Firestone's corporate headquarters is in Chicago andBridgestone's U.S. unit is in Nashville, the new company will bebased in Akron, where Firestone was founded in 1900.   John J. Nevin, Firestone chairman and chief executive officer,will serve as chairman of Bridgestone-Firestone until he isscheduled to retire next year, the company said.   Tokyo-based Bridgestone completed its $2.6 billion acquisitionof Firestone last April, and Firestone became Bridgestone's whollyowned subsidiary.</TEXT></DOC>